*Post-doctoral/engineer position on Big Data Analytics and Image=20
Processing for Satellite Ocean Sensing, Telecom Bretagne, Brest, France*

*Position: *18-month fellowship in the Signal and Communications=20
Department at Telecom Bretagne, Brest

*Context and objectives :*

The signal processing and remote sensing group of LabSTICC laboratory at=20
Telecom Bretagne, Brest, France (www.telecom-bretagne.eu) is seeking a=20
post-doctoral or engineer fellow on Big Data Analytics and Image=20
Processing for Satellite-based Ocean Remote Sensing. The successful=20
candidate will contribute to the definition, development and evaluation=20
of novel data-driven representations and algorithms for ocean remote=20
sensing applications, especially the spatio-temporal analysis and=20
reconstruction of high-resolution ocean dynamics from=20
multi-sensor/multi-scale satellite data. He will join a=20
transdisciplinary research group at the interface of computer science,=20
applied statistics, image processing and space oceanography, including=20
close collaborations with the Space Oceanography group (see Dr. Bertrand=20
Chapron, http://annuaire.ifremer.fr/cv/15870/en/) at Ifremer (French=20
Marine Research Institute) and two companies in the field of ocean=20
remote sensing, CLS (Collecte Localisation Satellite, www.cls.fr=20
<http://www.cls.fr>) and OceanDataLab (www.oceandatalab.com/=20
<http://www.oceandatalab.com/>). Information on our ongoing research may=20
be found at http://perso.telecom-bretagne.eu/ronanfablet/.


The successful candidate will focus on big data analytics within the=20
framework of Teralab big data platform (www.teralab-datascience.fr) and=20
address the scaling up and extensions of data-driven image processing=20
methodologies developed by our group for realistic large-scale=20
experiments with ocean remote sensing data.

*Requirements:*

Candidates will have a Ph.D in computer science with an experience in=20
Big Data Analytics and/or High-Performance Computing (e.g., Hadoop,=20
Spark, Mlib, Python/C/C++). Candidates with a Ph.D in signal/image=20
processing, or applied statistics and a good background in computer=20
science as well as a demonstrated interest in Big Data Analytics and Big=20
Data tools are also welcome. Applications of candidates with a=20
MSc./engineer degree and a strong potential for research will also be=20
positively considered. Previous experience of remote sensing data would=20
be a plus. Candidate should have a strong interest and commitment to=20
research. Creativity with an aim towards independent research is highly=20
emphasized.

*
Application :*

Send CV, statement of research interests and the contacts of references=20
to Prof. Ronan Fablet (*ronan.fablet@telecom-bretagne.eu*). Review of=20
applications will begin immediately and continue until the position is=20
filled.

*Additional information :*

*Expected starting date*: September 2015

*Duration*: 18 months

*Salary*: monthly net salary of about 2500=E2=82=AC (including mean annual=
=20
bonus) will be adjusted according to experience and qualification.


